text: In the quiet corners of the heart, where love's sweet whispers start, There lies a tale, a tale of old, in hushed tones, softly told.
A tale of two souls intertwined, in the labyrinth of time, A tale of the true romance, a dance of divine circumstance.
Oh, the true romance, it's not a fleeting glance, Nor a stolen kiss in a moonlit dance.
It's not the fiery passion that burns bright, Nor the sweet nothings whispered in the night.
The true romance is the silent song, That the heart hums when it's been too long.
It's the gentle touch, the comforting hold, The warmth that shields from the world's cold.
It's the shared laughter, the shared tears, The shared dreams over the years.
It's the shared silence, the shared word, The shared song of a lovebird.
The true romance is the steadfast gaze, That sees through life's confusing maze.
It's the tender look that speaks more, Than a thousand words ever bore.
It's the promise to stand, come what may, In the darkest night, or the brightest day.
It's the vow to love, to cherish, to care, In joy and sorrow, in despair.
The true romance is the soul's dance, In the rhythm of love's trance.
It's the melody that echoes in the heart, A symphony of love, a timeless art.
So here's to the true romance, the eternal flame, The love that remains, through joy and pain.
Here's to the love that stands the test of time, The true romance, the love divine.
